# Discord Chat Analysis

## 1. Summary
The chat primarily revolves around ElizaOS and its upcoming token migration, with some discussion about AI agents and x402 payment options. Odilitime confirmed that x402 currently accepts DEGENAI, AI16Z, or USDC on Base network, with plans to add ElizaOS token support after migration begins. There's mention of Solana integration being in testing phase. JustRahman introduced himself as a researcher studying AI agent pain points, seeking interviews with developers to understand challenges in wallet management, gas optimization, x402, and testing environments. The conversation also touched on website downtime (likely during updates) and some speculation about Nokia's AI investment plans. Skinny suggested a tokenomics model where each agent would only accept its native token or implement buyback mechanisms.

## 2. FAQ
Q: Any updates about the migration date? (asked by Seree) A: Unanswered
Q: With x402, is $degenai token used to pay? (asked by Skinny) A: you can use degenai, ai16z or USDC on base (answered by Odilitime)

## 3. Help Interactions
Helper: Seree | Helpee: ValleyBeyond | Context: Website being down | Resolution: Explained it's only down during updates
Helper: Odilitime | Helpee: Skinny | Context: Question about payment options for x402 | Resolution: Clarified that DEGENAI, AI16Z, or USDC on Base are accepted, with ElizaOS to be added after migration

## 4. Action Items
Technical: Add ElizaOS token support to x402 after migration begins | Description: Expand payment options for the x402 system | Mentioned By: Odilitime
Technical: Find a good Solana x402 client | Description: Currently testing Solana integration but haven't found suitable client | Mentioned By: Odilitime
Feature: Implement token-specific agent payments | Description: Each agent should only accept its token or implement buyback mechanisms | Mentioned By: Skinny

# Discord Chat Analysis: "core-devs" Channel

## 1. Summary:
This chat segment primarily focuses on development updates and sharing of resources related to the Eliza project. Key technical discussions include:

- A pull request (#6103) was shared for review
- Updates to the Spartan repository with two new commits on the v2-spartan-dev-neo branch
- Discussion about Exa websearch functionality, which is not currently implemented
- A Lit plugin update (plugin-lit) that includes encryption features, with subsequent discussion about code organization leading to the creation of a service instead of keeping libraries in actions
- Brief mention of a call with Coinbase regarding promotion on Base
- References to various agent communication protocols and standards, with concerns about overlap and potential confusion for new developers

The conversation is relatively fragmented with several links shared to external resources (Twitter/X posts, GitHub repositories) but limited in-depth technical discussion.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Do we have something that uses exa websearch currently? (asked by sayonara) A: No (answered by 0xbbjoker)
Q: Can we put Eliza on this? (asked by Neodotneo) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions:
Helper: cjft | Helpee: Odilitime | Context: Odilitime pointed out that having libraries in actions was weird in the Lit plugin code | Resolution: cjft acknowledged the feedback and created a service instead
